                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/8386</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Summerlin</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-19T21:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. Please ask an interview with President Carranza and say to him that the
                    President, upon the recommendation of Ambassador Fletcher, has ordered the
                    release of the 2,733,000 cartridges now detained at the border. The Ambassador
                    on his return to Mexico at the end of the month will arrange with President
                    Carranza details of delivery in order to prevent its falling in hands of the
                    revolutionists.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
